Now let me verify that `parse_event_type_label` handles the new variant through its serde fallthrough. The `parse_event_type_label` function has:
```rust
fn parse_event_type_label(label: &str) -> Result<EventType, String> {
    let event_type = match label {
        "RunStarted" | "run.started" => EventType::RunStarted,
        ...
        other => serde_json::from_value(Value::String(other.to_string()))
            .map_err(|e| format!("invalid event type '{other}': {e}"))?,
    };
    Ok(event_type)
}
```

The `other` fallthrough uses `serde_json::from_value(Value::String(...))`, which delegates to the `Deserialize` implementation of `EventType`. Since `EventType` uses `#[serde(rename_all = "PascalCase")]`, `AgentExitReason` will correctly serialize/deserialize as `"AgentExitReason"`. So no additional match arm is needed.

